RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 1 7F Dirt CR: 72. Maiden Claiming Purse 20600. FOR MAIDENS, FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Weight, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500, if for $10,000, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SEAN THE HAMMER took a quick lead and moved to the inside to rate the pace, was urged away leaving the five sixteenths pole then kept alert through the stretch. SPARKLING SHIRE came away a bit awkwardly then settled off the rail on the opening turn, picked up the chase from the three eighths pole, raced at the rail on the far turn and dueled for second past the eighth pole. CRYPTIC CODE raced well back toward the inside on the first turn, eased out leaving the turn and bid past the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn about the four path, swung to the outside entering the stretch and came along for third later yards. WILLIAM'S CAUSE stalked the early pace off the rail, picked up the chase leaving the three eighths pole, raced off the rail on the far turn then flattened in the lane. WICKOSITY raced off the pace about the four path, gave chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole but flattened in the three path of the far turn. DULINI raced well off the pace and off the rail the first turn, left the turn toward the outside and showed little response. TO LIVE IS TO LOVE saved ground.

ENTRY.NAME: William's Cause
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked off rail,chased 3/8,off rail far turn,flattened lane

ENTRY.NAME: Sean the Hammer
ENTRY.COMMENT: quick lead,rated pace inside,urged away 5/16,kept alert lane

ENTRY.NAME: Cryptic Code
ENTRY.COMMENT: well back inside,eased out 1/2,chased 3/8,4p far turn,along 3rd

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 2 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 83. Allowance Purse 35100. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Weight, 122 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since December 15 Allowed 4 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $12,500 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances)(W V A Races Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WHERE IS MIKE was bumped off stride at the break but dueled for the lead at the three eighths pole, drew clear past the five sixteenths and was kept alert through the stretch. MY BLUE EYES broke outward and took a brief early lead, dueled the winner leaving the three eighths pole, dropped back at the five sixteenths and rounded the turn about the three path, angled out leaving the turn then dug in through the stretch for second. BIGZ'S CABANA BOY chased inside, raced near the rail on the turn then outfinished in the stretch duel for second. GRAND ESCAPE gave chase through the backstretch, rounded the turn about the four path, eased out leaving the turn and ran evenly in the lane. HAGGERSDALE chased, raced near the rail on the turn and ran evenly in the stretch. SUPER KHOZAN was forced out leaving the gate then gave chase, raced off the rail on the turn, eased outward into the lane but showed little further. SPEIGHTS YOUR MIND broke in and made sharp contact with Where Is Mike, was slow getting into stride then saved ground.

ENTRY.NAME: Super Khozan
ENTRY.COMMENT: forced out start,chased,off rail turn,empty lane

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 3 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 57. Maiden Claiming Purse 13300. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Weight, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ASHARA briefly had the lead then gave chase from the half mile pole, recovered the advantage off the rail approaching the head of the lane and was steadily handled to widen. TAKE CHARGE LISA chased inside and raced near the rail on the turn, eased out to come between horses at the eighth pole and dueled clear for second later yards. GREAT DEVOTION chased through the backstretch, rounded the turn about the three path and relented second later yards. JO AMY chased outside, rounded the turn in the five path then flattened later yards. OUR GOLDEN COLLEEN chased through the backstretch, raced off the rail most of the turn but eased outward toward the head of the lane and showed little further. MAKO MISS gave chase, rounded the turn near the rail then flattened stride. AMERICAN LEGACY gave chase and rounded the turn about the three path. MY SILVER LADY took the lead at the half mile pole and rated the early pace, was caught at the rail approaching the eighth pole and weakened.

ENTRY.NAME: Our Golden Colleen
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased,off rail turn,eased out near 1/8,empty lane

ENTRY.NAME: Ashara
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased past 1/2,up off rail nearing 1/8,widened driving

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 4 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 86. Claiming Purse 15000. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Weight, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of Three Races At A Mile Or Over Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs. (W V A Races Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: REY O REYES stalked two deep then challenged toward the three eighths pole, dueled at even terms leaving the five sixteenths, raced two deep through the far turn and dueled determinedly to take the nod in late yards. OFFICER APPEAL rated a short lead inside, came under pressure nearing the three eighths pole and was met at even terms past the five sixteenths, contested the rail through the far turn and dug in gamely to deep stretch before reluctantly ceding. RIGHTEOUS MAN rounded the opening turn in the four path, started an outside bid leaving the seven sixteenths pole, raced in the four path on the far turn and came along for third inside the sixteenth pole. DOHKO raced in the four path the first turn then saved some ground on the second turn, picked up the chase nearing the three eighths pole, ran at the rail on the far turn and flattened in the lane. DIVINE PROPORTION saved ground, picked up the chase toward the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn off the rail then flattened in the lane. SIR TERRE settled about the three path and showed little response through the backstretch. MOUNTAIN TIME rounded the opening turn in the five path and settled off the pace from the seven eighths pole, raced in the four path on the second turn and showed little response leaving the half mile pole. HIGH PRINT saved ground and faded past the three eighths pole. The Steward reviewed, then dismissed, a claim of foul against the rider of Rey O Reyes for alleged interference in late stretch, lodged by the rider of Officer Appeal.

ENTRY.NAME: Divine Proportion
ENTRY.COMMENT: saved ground,chased near 3/8,off rail far turn,flattened

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 5 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 57. Maiden Special Weight Purse 32700. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 122 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GRUMPY'S BUDDY stalked the early pace from the three path, started a bid leaving the three eighths pole and raced close in the three and four paths of the far turn and dueled for the nod in later yards. LOVETHEBAND took the lead nearing the three quarter pole and moved to the inside to rate the pace, came under pressure approaching the three eighths, contested the edge just off the rail on the far turn and dueled at even terms from the eighth pole before relenting later yards. FUNKLE rated close inside, gave chase from the three eighths pole, raced at the rail on the far turn then flattened inside the eighth pole. KAYLEE'S SPITFIRE rounded the first turn about the four path and left the turn outside, gave chase nearing the seven sixteenths pole, raced in the four path of the far turn then flattened stride. DE'S CASTLE took a brief early lead while tapering in then stalked, gave chase toward the three eighths pole but dropped back midway on the far turn and weakened in the lane. CRUSH 'N RUN saved ground on the first turn, gave chase from the three eighths pole but weakened while losing ground on the far turn. JUBAY settled off the rail on the first turn, gave chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole but weakened off the rail on the far turn.

ENTRY.NAME: Lovetheband
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated pace inside,pressured 3/8,edge turn,relented later yards

ENTRY.NAME: De's Castle
ENTRY.COMMENT: briefly led,tapered in and stalked,chased 3/8,weakened lane

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 6 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 66. Claiming Purse 13300. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since January 15 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs. NO WVB CLAUSE.

CLAIM.OWNER: Pepe Stable and J L M Jacona Stable

RACE.FOOTNOTES: GRANDIOSELY accelerated to the front past the seven sixteenths pole and rated the pace, raced at the rail on the turn, came under pressure leaving the turn and widened through the lane. RED PRIESTESS pressured the pace through the backstretch, raced off the rail on the turn and settled for second. LILLY SIMONE chased through the backstretch, rounded the turn about the four path, was eased out leaving the turn then passed a rival while in an outward drift. QUEEN OF KANTHAROS ducked out and made contact with Treat Me Special leaving the gate, engaged in close chase through the backstretch, raced near the rail on the turn then flattened in the lane. JESS FOR KICKS angled to the inside to give chase, rounded the turn near the rail and showed little in the lane. BALLYMENA chased toward the outside, raced in the seven path of the turn then flattened stride widest. TREAT ME SPECIAL exchanged contact with Missing My Point leaving the gate then gave chase and rounded the turn in the three and four paths. YIRA gave chase toward mid track, raced in the five path of the turn and had little left in the lane. MISSING MY POINT exchanged contact with Treat Me Special leaving the gate then gave chase while saving ground.

ENTRY.NAME: Lilly Simone
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased outside,4p turn,eased out 1/8,drifted outward lane

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 7 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 62. Maiden Special Weight Purse 32700. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 122 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HAZEDNCONFUSED stalked from the four path the first turn, picked up the chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole, raced close off the rail on the far turn and dueled through the final sixteenth to inch away from BROAD IMAGINATION, who took over nearing the three quarter pole and moved to the inside to rate the pace, came under pressure leaving the seven sixteenths, rounded the far turn near the rail but was met leaving the sixteenth pole and relented; reluctantly. HE'S CLEVER settled off the rail on the first turn, gave chase from the nine sixteenths pole and rounded the far turn about the three path, eased to the outside leaving the turn and finished well to take third the final strides. JUST MURPHY rated close to the early pace inside, bid at the rail nearing the quarter pole, raced close through the upper stretch then flattened late yards. GATTO BE PROUD was reluctant to load, came out a step slow and brushed the gate on exit, rounded the first turn about the five path, raced outside into the backstretch and gave chase past the seven sixteenths pole, raced in the four path of the far turn and ran evenly in the lane. CURB THAT TIGER saved ground. TIME TO CHOOSE tapered in to stalk two deep, gave chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole but faded in the three path of the far turn. Harpersgonefishing flipped in the gate and was a late scratch.

ENTRY.NAME: Just Murphy
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated close inside,bid nearing 1/4,rail turn,flattened late yards

ENTRY.NAME: Broad Imagination
ENTRY.OWNER: Melton Christopher W and Mattingly Leonard

BERTRAM FLIGHT chased toward the inside, raced near the rail on the turn then flattened later yards. CATS DIAMOND BOY was hustled on the lead toward the inside, raced at the rail on the turn, drifted leaving the turn, was caught past the eighth pole and flattened the final sixteenth. TALKING TEDDY chased toward the inside, raced off the rail on the turn, eased out leaving the turn then steadied past the sixteenth pole. MIO GRACELAND chased inside, raced near the rail on the turn and ran evenly in the lane. DONNIE B broke a step slow, was never a factor and came through the lane in erratic paths. WINDSOR'S TRACKER was not a factor.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: MYGIDGETMARIE drew clear while tapering in through the backstretch and set a pressured pace, raced at the rail on the turn and was steadily handled to widen. HOLY HIP chased the early pace outside, raced near the rail on the turn and had to settle for second best. PRINCESS MIA ROSE came away a bit awkwardly and steadied from a narrowing opening toward the seven sixteenths pole, picked up the chase from the three eighths, raced at the rail on the turn and dueled through the stretch for third. RED LIL SHIPMENT chased toward the inside, raced at the rail on the turn, drifted leaving the turn and was outfinished in the stretch duel for third. FESSIN UP gave chase toward mid track, raced in the five path of the turn and ran evenly in the lane. BODIE'S STORM chased the early pace inside, rounded the turn off the rail and passed rivals in the lane. SUDDEN FLARE chased toward the outside, rounded the turn in the six path and flattened in the lane. MY BEST GIRL gave chase toward mid track, raced in the four path of the turn then weakened. NANNY'S MISSION gave chase toward the inside, rounded the turn near the rail and weakened in the lane.

ENTRY.NAME: Bodie's Storm
